humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: According to the pathology report, multiple (3) left axillary sentinel lymph nodes were excised and found to be negative for tumor (AJCC pN0(i-)). This indicates that there is no metastatic carcinoma in the sentinel lymph nodes, which aligns with New Rule 10 and New Rule 11. Therefore, the N stage for this patient's cancer is N0.

humanMachineDialogue.text: The report states that multiple (3) left axillary sentinel lymph nodes were excised and were negative for tumor (AJCC pN0). The immunohistochemical cytokeratin stain also confirmed the absence of tumor in the sentinel lymph nodes. Therefore, the pathologic N stage for this patient is N0.
